&lt;p&gt;Today after hours of debugging, I learned in the hard way that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A parent element is never able to cover (stack on top of) its child element if the parent has a z-index of any value, no matter how you change the child&apos;s CSS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How can I understand this behavior by logic? Is it in the specs?&lt;/p&gt;
